hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01HCi1U1THbYoFBSHCANXKGg\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01HCi1U1THbYoFBSHCANXKGg\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T20:12:11.846Z\",\"uuid\":\"e99e753a-ee06-45cd-a2d1-14230ec3e01e\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"18320c74-f436-4800-b013-e83d4d482368\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"db7b9129-3db7-42fe-bef7-fa13a713f44d\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/agent-integration-instructions\",\"slug\":\"glittery-crafting-harbor\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01HCi1U1THbYoFBSHCANXKGg\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Agent Integration Checklist\\n     2→\\n     3→This document provides requirements and a checklist for integrating new AI coding agents with Entire. Use this to validate your implementation is correct and complete.\\n     4→\\n     5→For step-by-step implementation instructions, code templates, and testing patterns, see the [Agent Implementation Guide](agent-guide.md).\\n     6→\\n     7→## Core Principle: Full Transcript Storage\\n     8→\\n     9→Entire stores the **complete session transcript** at every checkpoint, not incremental diffs. This enables:\\n    10→\\n    11→- Simple rewind: restore the full transcript, agent resumes from that state\\n    12→- No dependency on previous checkpoints being intact\\n    13→- Consistent behavior across all checkpoint types (committed, uncommitted)\\n    14→\\n    15→**Each checkpoint must contain the full session history up to that point.**\\n    16→\\n    17→## Core Principle: Native Format Preservation\\n    18→\\n    19→Store transcripts in the **agent's native format**. Any transformation or normalization should only be done to support CLI features (rewind, resume, summarization, file extraction), not for backend or web UI consumption.\\n    20→\\n    21→**Why:**\\n    22→- The backend/web UI should handle format differences, not the CLI\\n    23→- Transforming for downstream consumers couples the CLI to their requirements\\n    24→- Native formats ensure compatibility with agent's own import/export tools\\n    25→- Reduces risk of data loss from lossy transformations\\n    26→- Format changes that break the UI can be fixed with a backend deploy; CLI changes require a full release cycle and user adoption\\n    27→\\n    28→**Do:**\\n    29→- Store the raw transcript as the agent produces it\\n    30→- Parse the native format when CLI features need specific data (e.g., extract file paths for `entire status`)\\n    31→- Let the backend normalize formats for display\\n    32→\\n    33→**Don't:**\\n    34→- Create a \\\"universal transcript format\\\" in the CLI\\n    35→- Transform logs to match what the web UI expects\\n    36→- Strip or restructure data to simplify backend processing\\n    37→- Create intermediate formats (e.g., converting JSON to JSONL for \\\"easier parsing\\\")\\n    38→- Reconstruct transcripts from events when a canonical export exists\\n    39→\\n    40→## Integration Checklist\\n    41→\\n    42→### Transcript Capture\\n    43→\\n    44→See Guide: [Transcript Format Guide](agent-guide.md#transcript-format-guide), [TranscriptAnalyzer](agent-guide.md#transcriptanalyzer), [TranscriptPreparer](agent-guide.md#transcriptpreparer)\\n    45→\\n    46→- [ ] **Full transcript on every turn**: At turn-end, capture the complete session transcript, not just events since the last checkpoint\\n    47→- [ ] **Resumed session handling**: When a user resumes an existing session, the transcript must include all historical messages, not just new ones since the plugin/hook loaded\\n    48→- [ ] **Use agent's canonical export**: Prefer the agent's native export command (e.g., reading Claude's JSONL file, Gemini's JSON) over manually reconstructing from events\\n    49→- [ ] **No custom formats**: Store the agent's native format directly in `NativeData` - do not convert between formats (e.g., JSON to JSONL) or create intermediate representations\\n    50→- [ ] **Graceful degradation**: If the canonical source is unavailable (e.g., agent shutting down), fall back to best-effort capture with clear documentation of limitations\\n    51→\\n    52→### Session Storage Abstraction\\n    53→\\n    54→See Guide: [Step 3 - Core Agent Interface](agent-guide.md#step-3-implement-core-agent-interface-youragentgo)\\n    55→\\n    56→- [ ] **`WriteSession` implementation**: Agent must implement `WriteSession(AgentSession)` to restore sessions\\n    57→- [ ] **File-based agents** (Claude, Gemini): Write `NativeData` to `SessionRef` path\\n    58→- [ ] **Database-backed agents**: Write `NativeData` to file, then import into native storage (the native format should be what the agent's import command expects)\\n    59→- [ ] **Single format per agent**: Store only the agent's native format in `NativeData` - no separate fields for different representations of the same data\\n    60→\\n    61→### Hook Events\\n    62→\\n    63→See Guide: [Step 4 - ParseHookEvent](agent-guide.md#step-4-implement-parsehookevent-lifecyclego), [Event Mapping Reference](agent-guide.md#event-mapping-reference)\\n    64→\\n    65→Map agent-native hooks to these `EventType` constants (see `agent/event.go`):\\n    66→\\n    67→- [ ] **TurnStart**: Fire when user submits a prompt (for pre-prompt state capture)\\n    68→- [ ] **TurnEnd**: Fire when agent finishes responding (for checkpoint creation)\\n    69→- [ ] **SessionStart**: Fire when a new session begins\\n    70→- [ ] **SessionEnd**: Fire when session is explicitly ended (optional but recommended)\\n    71→\\n    72→### Rewind/Resume Support\\n    73→\\n    74→- [ ] **Rewind restores full state**: After rewind, agent can continue from that point with full context\\n    75→- [ ] **Resume command**: `FormatResumeCommand()` returns the CLI command to resume a session\\n    76→- [ ] **Session ID preservation**: Restored sessions maintain original session ID where possible\\n    77→\\n    78→### Testing\\n    79→\\n    80→See Guide: [Testing Patterns](agent-guide.md#testing-patterns)\\n    81→\\n    82→- [ ] **New session**: Create session, multiple turns, verify full transcript at each checkpoint\\n    83→- [ ] **Resumed session**: Resume existing session, add turns, verify checkpoint includes historical messages\\n    84→- [ ] **Rewind**: Rewind to earlier checkpoint, verify agent can continue from that state\\n    85→- [ ] **Agent shutdown**: Verify graceful handling if agent exits during checkpoint\\n    86→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"95183ed2-0b31-4e7e-a43c-2b34b9497df4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T20:12:11.845Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md\",\"content\":\"# Agent Integration Checklist\\n\\nThis document provides requirements and a checklist for integrating new AI coding agents with Entire. Use this to validate your implementation is correct and complete.\\n\\nFor step-by-step implementation instructions, code templates, and testing patterns, see the [Agent Implementation Guide](agent-guide.md).\\n\\n## Core Principle: Full Transcript Storage\\n\\nEntire stores the **complete session transcript** at every checkpoint, not incremental diffs. This enables:\\n\\n- Simple rewind: restore the full transcript, agent resumes from that state\\n- No dependency on previous checkpoints being intact\\n- Consistent behavior across all checkpoint types (committed, uncommitted)\\n\\n**Each checkpoint must contain the full session history up to that point.**\\n\\n## Core Principle: Native Format Preservation\\n\\nStore transcripts in the **agent's native format**. Any transformation or normalization should only be done to support CLI features (rewind, resume, summarization, file extraction), not for backend or web UI consumption.\\n\\n**Why:**\\n- The backend/web UI should handle format differences, not the CLI\\n- Transforming for downstream consumers couples the CLI to their requirements\\n- Native formats ensure compatibility with agent's own import/export tools\\n- Reduces risk of data loss from lossy transformations\\n- Format changes that break the UI can be fixed with a backend deploy; CLI changes require a full release cycle and user adoption\\n\\n**Do:**\\n- Store the raw transcript as the agent produces it\\n- Parse the native format when CLI features need specific data (e.g., extract file paths for `entire status`)\\n- Let the backend normalize formats for display\\n\\n**Don't:**\\n- Create a \\\"universal transcript format\\\" in the CLI\\n- Transform logs to match what the web UI expects\\n- Strip or restructure data to simplify backend processing\\n- Create intermediate formats (e.g., converting JSON to JSONL for \\\"easier parsing\\\")\\n- Reconstruct transcripts from events when a canonical export exists\\n\\n## Integration Checklist\\n\\n### Transcript Capture\\n\\nSee Guide: [Transcript Format Guide](agent-guide.md#transcript-format-guide), [TranscriptAnalyzer](agent-guide.md#transcriptanalyzer), [TranscriptPreparer](agent-guide.md#transcriptpreparer)\\n\\n- [ ] **Full transcript on every turn**: At turn-end, capture the complete session transcript, not just events since the last checkpoint\\n- [ ] **Resumed session handling**: When a user resumes an existing session, the transcript must include all historical messages, not just new ones since the plugin/hook loaded\\n- [ ] **Use agent's canonical export**: Prefer the agent's native export command (e.g., reading Claude's JSONL file, Gemini's JSON) over manually reconstructing from events\\n- [ ] **No custom formats**: Store the agent's native format directly in `NativeData` - do not convert between formats (e.g., JSON to JSONL) or create intermediate representations\\n- [ ] **Graceful degradation**: If the canonical source is unavailable (e.g., agent shutting down), fall back to best-effort capture with clear documentation of limitations\\n\\n### Session Storage Abstraction\\n\\nSee Guide: [Step 3 - Core Agent Interface](agent-guide.md#step-3-implement-core-agent-interface-youragentgo)\\n\\n- [ ] **`WriteSession` implementation**: Agent must implement `WriteSession(AgentSession)` to restore sessions\\n- [ ] **File-based agents** (Claude, Gemini): Write `NativeData` to `SessionRef` path\\n- [ ] **Database-backed agents**: Write `NativeData` to file, then import into native storage (the native format should be what the agent's import command expects)\\n- [ ] **Single format per agent**: Store only the agent's native format in `NativeData` - no separate fields for different representations of the same data\\n\\n### Hook Events\\n\\nSee Guide: [Step 4 - ParseHookEvent](agent-guide.md#step-4-implement-parsehookevent-lifecyclego), [Event Mapping Reference](agent-guide.md#event-mapping-reference)\\n\\nMap agent-native hooks to these `EventType` constants (see `agent/event.go`):\\n\\n- [ ] **TurnStart**: Fire when user submits a prompt (for pre-prompt state capture)\\n- [ ] **TurnEnd**: Fire when agent finishes responding (for checkpoint creation)\\n- [ ] **SessionStart**: Fire when a new session begins\\n- [ ] **SessionEnd**: Fire when session is explicitly ended (optional but recommended)\\n\\n### Rewind/Resume Support\\n\\n- [ ] **Rewind restores full state**: After rewind, agent can continue from that point with full context\\n- [ ] **Resume command**: `FormatResumeCommand()` returns the CLI command to resume a session\\n- [ ] **Session ID preservation**: Restored sessions maintain original session ID where possible\\n\\n### Testing\\n\\nSee Guide: [Testing Patterns](agent-guide.md#testing-patterns)\\n\\n- [ ] **New session**: Create session, multiple turns, verify full transcript at each checkpoint\\n- [ ] **Resumed session**: Resume existing session, add turns, verify checkpoint includes historical messages\\n- [ ] **Rewind**: Rewind to earlier checkpoint, verify agent can continue from that state\\n- [ ] **Agent shutdown**: Verify graceful handling if agent exits during checkpoint\\n\",\"numLines\":86,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":86}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"18320c74-f436-4800-b013-e83d4d482368\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"95183ed2-0b31-4e7e-a43c-2b34b9497df4\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"db7b9129-3db7-42fe-bef7-fa13a713f44d\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/agent-integration-instructions\",\"slug\":\"glittery-crafting-harbor\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_0146Xv36EDLWBWP8iZcFt11e\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01CwS5vyGG3BACjnpcayKdgs\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/docs/architecture/agent-guide.md\",\"limit\":5},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":364,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":110137,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":364},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYKvw2oUJSrznMxpz6KGC\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"285317df-5d20-44ef-995b-79782af882e6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T20:12:12.331Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"285317df-5d20-44ef-995b-79782af882e6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"db7b9129-3db7-42fe-bef7-fa13a713f44d\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/agent-integration-instructions\",\"slug\":\"glittery-crafting-harbor\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CwS5vyGG3BACj